{
  "title": "Smack",
  "children": [
    {
      "title": "Overview",
      "lines": [
        "Loop glitcher for",
        "live audio.",
        "",
        "Grabs a quantized",
        "loop of whatever is",
        "upstream, slices it,",
        "and rolls seeded",
        "random FX plus a",
        "new slice order.",
        "",
        "The pattern repeats",
        "each pass until you",
        "re-roll it.",
        "",
        "Works in chain slots",
        "and Master FX."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Quick Start",
      "lines": [
        "1. Set Loop Len.",
        "2. Play something.",
        "3. Hit Capture to",
        " grab the last",
        " loop length.",
        "4. A/B to punch",
        " between clean",
        " and pattern.",
        "5. Re-Roll for a",
        " new pattern.",
        "",
        "Or: Arm, then play.",
        "Recording starts on",
        "the next step and",
        "stops after the",
        "loop length."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Knobs",
      "children": [
        {
          "title": "Chain UI Knobs",
          "lines": [
            "In the chain editor",
            "knobs 1-8 are:",
            "",
            "1: FX Density",
            "2: Order Density",
            "3: Loop Length",
            "4: Slice Res",
            "5: Wet",
            "6: Pitch Range",
            "7: AB Quantize",
            "8: Seed",
            "",
            "Hold Shift: knob",
            "page 2 (Pan L/R,",
            "Channels, Transport,",
            "BPM, Monitor, Pads,",
            "Pad Rate); the",
            "steps show only the",
            "pinned slices.",
            "",
            "Wet = loop vs dry",
            "crossfade (this",
            "build processes the",
            "chain's audio)."
          ]
        },
        {
          "title": "Knob Pages",
          "lines": [
            "On Master FX and",
            "the param pages:",
            "",
            "Main knobs 1-8:",
            "FX Density, Order,",
            "Loop Len, Slice Res,",
            "Wet, Pitch Range,",
            "AB Quantize, Seed.",
            "",
            "Perform knobs 1-8:",
            "A/B, FX, Order, Wet,",
            "Pitch, AB Quantize,",
            "Pad Play, Pad Rate.",
            "Capture, Arm, Roll,",
            "Clear, Detect BPM:",
            "select in the list.",
            "",
            "Setup knobs 1-8:",
            "Wet, Pitch Range,",
            "AB Quantize, Seed,",
            "Transport, Channels,",
            "Pan L, Pan R."
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Pads & Steps",
      "lines": [
        "Bottom-left pads:",
        "",
        "Capture: retro-grab",
        " (green)",
        "Arm: record next",
        " step (red)",
        "A/B: clean loop or",
        " pattern (white)",
        "Re-Roll: new",
        " pattern (blue)",
        "Clear: drop loop",
        " (orange, above",
        " Capture)",
        "",
        "Hardware Capture",
        "button: retro-grab.",
        "",
        "Steps 1-16 show the",
        "slice pattern, one",
        "color per effect,",
        "white is playhead.",
        "Press a step to",
        "mute its effect;",
        "press again to",
        "restore it.",
        "",
        "HOLD Re-Roll to",
        "clear every pinned",
        "slice and roll a",
        "fresh pattern.",
        "",
        "Loops over 16",
        "slices:",
        "5th bottom pad steps",
        "through 16-slice",
        "pages.",
        "",
        "HOLD A/B: momentary",
        "punch — flips while",
        "held, snaps back on",
        "release."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Effects",
      "lines": [
        "22 slice effects:",
        "",
        "retrigger, reverse,",
        "pitch (varispeed),",
        "half/double speed,",
        "gate chop, buzz,",
        "bitcrush, repeat",
        "after split, reverse",
        "after split,",
        "tape stop and start,",
        "vinyl scratch,",
        "envelope shapes,",
        "pan tricks, filter",
        "sweeps, vowel",
        "filter, tonal delay,",
        "granular freeze,",
        "synced delay and",
        "ping-pong,",
        "distortion, phaser,",
        "gated reverb.",
        "",
        "FX Density sets how",
        "many slices get an",
        "effect; Order sets",
        "slice reshuffling."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Dual Mono",
      "lines": [
        "Channels (Setup):",
        "Stereo or Dual Mono.",
        "",
        "Dual Mono treats L",
        "and R inputs as two",
        "mono signals, each",
        "with its own effect",
        "pattern, panned",
        "into the stereo",
        "field (Pan L/Pan R).",
        "",
        "Bottom pad row 7:",
        "toggle the mode.",
        "Pad 8: tap = edit L",
        "or R lane; hold +",
        "knob 1 or 2 = pans.",
        "",
        "A side plays the",
        "raw stereo loop;",
        "B side plays the",
        "panned lanes."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Seed & Re-Roll",
      "lines": [
        "Seed browses",
        "patterns by number:",
        "the same seed always",
        "gives the same",
        "pattern.",
        "",
        "Re-Roll varies the",
        "current seed for a",
        "fresh pattern; dial",
        "the Seed knob to",
        "return to the",
        "canonical one."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "BPM Detect",
      "lines": [
        "Shift + Re-Roll",
        "listens to the last",
        "8 seconds of input",
        "and detects its",
        "tempo (60-180 BPM).",
        "",
        "The result becomes",
        "the free-run tempo,",
        "so Capture grabs",
        "true bars of the",
        "source. Shown as",
        "@BPM in the title.",
        "",
        "MIDI clock always",
        "wins when running.",
        "Needs material with",
        "clear hits; pads",
        "and drones report",
        "no tempo."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Sync & Transport",
      "lines": [
        "Set Move's MIDI",
        "Clock to Out so",
        "Smack locks to the",
        "transport (same as",
        "the Arp).",
        "",
        "Without it, Smack",
        "free-runs at the",
        "project tempo.",
        "",
        "Transport (Setup):",
        "Follow: Move stop",
        "pauses the loop,",
        "play restarts it.",
        "Free: keep looping."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Presets",
      "lines": [
        "Module presets save",
        "all knobs, the seed",
        "and re-roll state,",
        "plus slice mutes.",
        "",
        "Audio is not saved:",
        "capture a new loop",
        "after loading."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Web Editor",
      "lines": [
        "The chain FX build",
        "has no browser page",
        "(host limit: only",
        "synth slots + tools",
        "get custom web UI).",
        "",
        "Use smack-in or",
        "oversmack for the",
        "browser editor.",
        "",
        "Pin with parameter:",
        "lock_slice takes",
        "'effect:param' too."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Screen Reader",
      "lines": [
        "With the screen",
        "reader on (Global",
        "Settings), the chain",
        "editor announces",
        "pads, knob changes",
        "and loop state."
      ]
    }
  ]
}
